.TH BDFS_DAEMON 8 "2025" "bdfs 1.0.0" "BTRFS+DwarFS Framework"
.SH NAME
bdfs_daemon \- BTRFS+DwarFS framework userspace daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bdfs_daemon
[\fB\-f\fR]
[\fB\-c\fR \fIctl_device\fR]
[\fB\-s\fR \fIsocket_path\fR]
[\fB\-d\fR \fIstate_dir\fR]
[\fB\-j\fR \fIthreads\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bdfs_daemon
bridges the
.B btrfs_dwarfs
kernel module and the userspace tools
.RB ( mkdwarfs ,
.BR dwarfs ,
.BR dwarfsextract ,
.BR btrfs ).
.PP
It listens on the bdfs netlink socket for events emitted by the kernel module
and dispatches the corresponding tool pipelines via a worker thread pool.
It also exposes a Unix domain socket for the
.BR bdfs (1)
CLI tool.
.PP
The daemon must be running for any
.BR bdfs (1)
command that modifies filesystem state to complete. Commands that only read
state (e.g.
.BR "bdfs partition list" ,
.BR "bdfs status" )
communicate directly with the kernel module via
.I /dev/bdfs_ctl
and do not require the daemon.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f
Run in the foreground (do not daemonize). Useful for debugging.
.TP
.BI \-c " device"
Control device path. Default:
.IR /dev/bdfs_ctl .
.TP
.BI \-s " path"
Unix socket path for CLI communication. Default:
.IR /run/bdfs/daemon.sock .
.TP
.BI \-d " dir"
State directory. Default:
.IR /var/lib/bdfs .
.TP
.BI \-j " N"
Number of worker threads. Default: 4.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose logging to syslog.
.SH OPERATION
.SS Event Loop
The daemon runs a
.BR select (2)
loop over two file descriptors:
.IP \(bu 4
The netlink socket (protocol 31), receiving
.B bdfs_event
messages from the kernel module.
.IP \(bu 4
The Unix domain socket, accepting connections from the
.BR bdfs (1)
CLI.
.SS Worker Pool
Incoming events are translated into
.B bdfs_job
structures and enqueued to a FIFO job queue. Worker threads dequeue jobs and
execute the appropriate tool pipeline:
.TP
.B BDFS_JOB_EXPORT_TO_DWARFS
.nf
btrfs subvolume snapshot \-r <subvol> <tmp>
btrfs send <tmp> | btrfs receive <extract_dir>
mkdwarfs \-i <extract_dir> \-o <image.dwarfs.tmp>
rename(<image.dwarfs.tmp>, <final_path>)
.fi
.TP
.B BDFS_JOB_IMPORT_FROM_DWARFS
.nf
btrfs subvolume create <dest>
dwarfsextract \-i <image.dwarfs> \-o <dest>
.fi
.TP
.B BDFS_JOB_MOUNT_DWARFS
.nf
dwarfs <image.dwarfs> <mountpoint> \-o cache_size=<N>m
.fi
.TP
.B BDFS_JOB_STORE_IMAGE
.nf
copy_file_range(src_fd, dst_fd)   # reflink on same BTRFS
.fi
.TP
.B BDFS_JOB_SNAPSHOT_CONTAINER
.nf
btrfs subvolume snapshot [\-r] <subvol> <snapshot>
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/bdfs_ctl
Kernel module control device. The daemon opens this at startup.
.TP
.I /run/bdfs/daemon.sock
Unix domain socket. Created at startup, removed at shutdown.
.TP
.I /var/lib/bdfs/
State directory. Stores temporary files during export/import operations.
.TP
.I /etc/bdfs/bdfs.conf
Configuration file. See
.BR bdfs.conf (5).
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown. Waits for in-progress jobs to complete.
.TP
.B SIGINT
Same as SIGTERM.
.TP
.B SIGPIPE
Ignored.
.SH SYSTEMD
A systemd service unit is installed at
.IR /lib/systemd/system/bdfs_daemon.service .
.nf
systemctl enable \-\-now bdfs_daemon
.fi
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The daemon logs to syslog with facility
.BR LOG_DAEMON .
To view logs:
.nf
journalctl \-u bdfs_daemon \-f
.fi
.PP
Run in the foreground with
.B \-f \-v
for verbose output during development.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bdfs (1),
.BR mkdwarfs (1),
.BR dwarfs (1),
.BR dwarfsextract (1),
.BR btrfs (8)
.SH AUTHORS
BTRFS+DwarFS Framework Contributors.
